```sql
-- Deduplicate billing_events: one row per subscription + event_month combination
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- int_subscriptions_with_plan.sql
```sql
-- Enrich subscriptions with plan tier, handle missing plans
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status,
    tier
FROM source
```

-- Determine active subscriptions by month: started by month and either not ended or ended after month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.tier,
        DATE_TRUNC('month', s.started_at)::DATE AS month
    FROM {{ ref('int_subscriptions_with_plan') }} s
    WHERE s.started_at IS NOT NULL
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    tier,
    month
FROM source

-- Monthly subscription metrics: active subscriptions, total MRR, unique users by tier and industry
WITH billing_joined AS (
    SELECT
        b.subscription_id,
        b.event_month,
        b.amount,
        s.user_id,
        s.tier,
        u.industry
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} b
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_subscriptions_with_plan') }} s
        ON s.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_users_with_company') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
)
SELECT
    b.event_month AS month,
    b.tier,
    b.industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT b.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(b.amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT b.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM billing_joined b
GROUP BY
    b.event_month,
    b.tier,
    b.industry
ORDER BY
    b.event_month,
    b.tier,
    b.industry
